Q1.   Write a python script to store multiple items in a single variable(items are "Java","python","SQL","C") using tuple.
Ans.   t1=("Java","pyhton","SQL","C")

Q2.   Write a python program to store only one item using tuple.
Ans.   t1=tuple(input("Enter a number: ").split(','))

Q3.   Write a python program to reverse the tuple.
Ans.   t1=tuple(input("Enter any object sereted by comma: ").split(',')
       print(t1[::-1])
       
Q4.   Write a python program to swap two tuple in python.
Ans.   t1=tuple(("Enter object sepreted by comma: ").split(','))
       t2=tuple(("Enter object sepreted by comma: ").split(','))
       t3=()
       t3=t1
       t1=t2
       t2=t3
       print(t1,t2)
       
//Q5.   Write a python program to check if all items are in the tuple are the same.
Ans.     s1=[1005,1005,1005,154,1005,120]
         a=s1[0]
         flag=0
         for i in s1:
             if(a==i):
               flag=0
             else:
               break
         if flag==1:
            print("all the item isn't same")
         else:
            print("All the item are same")
       
